Description: Up for bid is a vintage Dean Cadillac semi hollow body guitar in excellent condition. This very high quality made guitar has two small dents on the bottom. One dent measures 3/8 inch by 3/8 inch and the other dent ¼ inch by 1/8 inch. It has vintage Seymour Duncan pickups, has very nice vintage Deluxe tuning pegs which are German made. The fake ivory inlay on the fret board has wear. Serial number 960717 is marked on the 23rd fret. It maintains all of its original screws. The neck is built in and not bolted. It has a great action and plays very well plugged up to an amp. It maintains its original volume knobs that function well and its pickup switch functions well. It needs a new set of strings and has a plain tremolo. This guitar comes with a gig bag. An excellent vintage Dean guitar!
